title: Crudités with Green Goddess Dip
summary: Crudités with Green Goddess Dip is a gluten free, primal, and pescatarian side dish. One serving contains 317 calories, 13g of protein, and 21g of fat. This recipe serves 10 and costs $2.71 per serving. This recipe from Epicurious has 1 fans. It can be enjoyed any time, but it is especially good for The Super Bowl. If you have wine vinegar, american shrimp, garlic clove, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 45 minutes. With a spoonacular score of 67%, this dish is good. Similar recipes include Green Goddess Dip with Crudités, Crudités And Shrimp With Green Goddess Dip, and Fall Crudites with Green Goddess Dressing.
instructions: Preparation                                                        Combine lemon juice, anchovies, shallot,vinegar, and garlic in processor. Blend untilshallot and garlic are finely chopped. Addavocado, sour cream, parsley, tarragon,and basil; blend until almost smooth. Withmachine running, add olive oil through feedtube in thin stream. Transfer dip to smallbowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper.DO AHEAD:  Can be made 1 day ahead.Cover and chill.                                                                Place bowl of dip on large platter.Surround with shrimp and vegetables.
